      "type": "Activity",
      "name": "FEA ensemble simulation of F1717 compression-bending protocol",
      "description": "A high-fidelity finite element ensemble (three independent solver environments: FDA in-house, Ansys Mechanical, and DePuy Synthes proprietary) was executed to predict stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement under simulated ASTM F1717 loading. The simulation team noted that the ensemble spread was narrow (<2%) and argued that the numerical predictions are functionally equivalent to a physical experiment given the tight inter-laboratory agreement among the three solver solutions. On this basis the ensemble simulation output was submitted as the primary evidence supporting the QoI acceptance criteria, supplementing — and in this submission effectively replacing — the bench-test comparison for the yield-force QoI.",
      "activityType": "numerical-simulation"
    }
